description:
With the Elite Graduate Programme, successful candidates are provided with an opportunity to gain practical experience through real-world projects and develop critical IT and life skills over a 12-month period while earning a stipend.
 
Applications require an IT-related Bachelors Degree or Advanced Diploma.Requirements:
Candidates require one of the following:Bachelors Degree with Information Technology related subject(s); 
Advanced Diploma with Information Technology related subjects; 
Matric plus VZAP- , LUSO-, TDF-, or similar certification (including Computer Science Certification).

The Western Cape Government: Corporate Services Centre invites unemployed South African graduates residing in the Western Cape to apply for the Graduate Programme for 2023/2024.
 
The Graduate Programme is a Youth Development Programme which will provide successful interns the opportunity to gain practical work experience for a period of 3-24 months.
 
Requirements:You are in possession of a completed Certificate (NQF 5) or Diploma (NQF 6) or Degree (NQF 7) or Post Graduate Qualification (NQF 8 and higher);
You are a South African citizen and reside in the Western Cape;
You are between the ages of 20 and 35;
You desire an opportunity to gain practical work experience.
Skills and Competencies:Good communication (written and verbal) skills in at least two of the official languages of the Western Cape;
Proven computer literacy (MS Office);
Ability to operate office equipment;
Planning and organising skills.

Safair Operations, operating as FlySafair has a vacancy for a Refund Intern at our head office in Bonaero Park (Gauteng - Kempton Park).  The successful applicant will report to the Manager: Finance
 
Reference number: JHB000717Responsibilities:Allocating payment to bookings that doesn’t reflect on reservation system;
Correcting bookings on the reservation system where the charges and payments do not agree;
Assess and process refund requests based on the refund policy;
Assisting  customer/ passengers both verbally and in writing regarding payments and refund queries;
Adhoc duties as requested.
Requirements:Grade 12 / Matric
Must have a Diploma or Degree
No criminal or credit record.
Solid computer literacy
Excellent communication in English – speak, read and write
Excellent phone etiquette 
Skills and Competencies:Excellent understanding in delivering great customer service to a customer;
High degree of patience and assertiveness;
Conflict resolution skills;
The ability to work well under pressure;
Practice good time management skills and willingness to work longer than normal office hours;
Good mathematical skills;
Customer focused and service oriented.

The City of Johannesburg (CoJ) is offering Internship opportunities to suitably qualified and unemployed graduates. The Interships will run for a a period NOT exceeding eighteen (18) months.
 
 
The following Internship Opportunities are open for applications:
 
Finance Intern
Salary: R9 043,21 pm
Requirements: Grade 12 (NQF level 4) plus tertiary qualification in Finance / Accounting or equivalent qualification.
Duties: Control and coordinate the implementation of specific procedures systems and controls Asset Management associated with functional areas embodied in the Community Development department. Handle all Supply Chain Management processes associated to COJ policies and procedures. Manage and control specific Budgeting, Expenditure and accounting procedures associated with Financial reportingSports and Recreation Intern
Salary: R9 043,21 pm
Requirements: Grade 12 (NQF level 4) plus relevant tertiary qualification, with specific focus on Sports and Recreation/NQF level 6;
Duties: Provide support in events management and activities at sport facility. Assist Managers / Office in dealing with follow ups on community requests and queries. Assist in the initiation of programmes and sport-related activities. Marketing and Social Media Communication Liaison. Conduct research of innovative and new trends in Sports & recreationSkills and Competencies:High level of Confidentially and organisation skills;
Ability to work under pressure and Independently;
Ability to prioritise;
Sound numerical ability;
Good time management skills;
Finance Reporting

Artscape invites graduates to apply for an (EPWP) Internship opportunity in our Supply Chain Management department as an SCM Administrator Intern.
 
The Intern will report to the Supply Chain Manager for the duration of the internship. A monthly report will be required from the intern to be sent to HR.
 
Responsibilities:Assisting with sourcing of quotations;
Capturing of requisitions;
Making follow ups on outstanding commitments for goods/service & deliveries;
Assisting with general administration of the SCM and Finance departments;
Arranging & attending meetings with internal & external project managers & taking of accurate minutes of meeting;
Assist with bidding processes and administration;
Provide administrative support to the bidding committees;
Communicate with end users on status of Purchase Orders and potential delays 
RequirementsMust have a National Diploma/Degree:
Supply Chain Management
Public Procurement Management
Public Management
Grade 12 Certificate (Statement of Results must be attached)
Must be residing in the Western Cape (Proof of residential address to be attached)
Must be between the ages 18 – 25;
Be a South African citizen;
The candidate must be articulate in 2 or 3 of the Western Cape’s predominant languages (i.e. English, Afrikaans, or IsiXhosa);
Must have no previous criminal conviction(s) or case(s) pending; 
Advantageous: Previous experience in any discipline of the Performing Arts will be advantageous;Skills and Competencies:Must be Computer literate with advanced competencies in Excel/ Word/power point /outlook and publisher;
Must be able to work with in a team;
Proficient in English (written);
Creative thinking;
Excellent interpersonal skills;
Superb time management skills

We run two four-week programmes a year in the winter (June/July) and summer (January) university holidays. It’s a paid, in-office programme that may lead to a permanent position, depending on company needs and the right fit.
 
As part of the team at Electrum, you get:to be involved in the full life cycle of our projects;
professional training and on-the-job learning;
mentorship from industry experts;
a workplace with an innovative office culture;
to work on real customer problems;
access to extensive career growth opportunities;
valuable work experience in a real FinTech environment, where you get to work on real projects. 
Requirements:Computer Science, Engineering, Maths or Physics student in either their 2nd, 3rd or Honours year (preference is given to Honours and 3rd year students).
A minimum average of 65% for all modules.
Experience working with Java at university or from personal projects.
Understanding fundamentals of object-oriented programming.
Excellent interpersonal skills.
Here are some of the benefits we offer:Flexible work hours.
Onsite gym and shower facilities.
Daily cooked lunches and a stocked kitchen for the afternoon nibbles.
Team socialising like hikes, getaways, and dinners.
A generous leave policy, starting at 20 days per year.
A recreational area with foosball, table tennis and an Oculus.
Fatsaks scattered around the office for deep thinking or meditation.
